# A Simple Guide for Manually Setting Up an Ubuntu Server
### Screen
Use screen for updating & upgrading system.
`
sudo apt-get install screen
screen
screen -list
screen -raAd
`
Ctrl+A+D detach screen
To scroll within screen, press Ctrl-Esc to enter cursor mode. You can then scroll down and up with j and k. Press Esc again to exit cursor mode.

### Update & Upgrade Server
`sudo add-apt-repository universe`
`apt update && apt upgrade -y && apt autoremove -y && apt autoclean && apt clean`
`sudo apt install -y curl nano certbot cron ufw htop dialog`
`sudo journalctl --vacuum-size=50M`
